item.title: CVE-2023-22577|2023-04-25T09:21:52.273Z -- cern -- white%20rabbit%20switch
item.description: Within White Rabbit Switch it's possible as an unauthenticated user to retrieve sensitive information such as password hashes and the SNMP community strings.

item.title: CVE-2023-22581|2023-04-25T09:21:51.881Z -- cern -- white%20rabbit%20switch
item.description: White Rabbit Switch contains a vulnerability which makes it possible for an attacker to perform system commands under the context of the web application (the default installation makes the webserver run as the root user).
